&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONSULTANTS IN CARDIOTHORACIC ANAESTHESIA AND CRITICAL CARE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE JAMES COOK UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL, MIDDLESBROUGH &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South Tees NHS Foundation Trust are recruiting Consultants in Cardiothoracic Anaesthesia to join our existing team of 13 Consultants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dynamic forward thinking cardiothoracic anaesthetists to join us and continue the development of the service. You will join a friendly, committed team to provide anaesthesia and critical care for approximately 1000 cardiac and 700 thoracic cases per year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our varied caseload includes minimally invasive aortic and mitral surgery, major aortic work, an established TAVI programme, VAT lobectomies, thymectomies and robotic thoracic surgery. A robotic mitral surgery programme is in the planning stages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Tees Valley is home to vibrant towns, picturesque villages, breathtaking countryside and stunning coastlines and has the North York Moors National Park on its doorstep. Excellent travel links mean London and Edinburgh are both just a couple of hours away by train.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recently rated as one of the best trusts in the country for patient safety and one of the best places to work, South Tees Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is one of the largest Foundation Trusts in England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should possess full GMC registration, FRCA (or equivalent) and either already be on the Specialist Register or be within 6 months of receiving their Certificate of Completion of Training (CCT) at the time of interview. You must have advanced experience in cardiothoracic anaesthesia and cardiothoracic critical care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
